ciscoEnhancedIpsecFlowMIB.description: This is a MIB Module for monitoring the structures and status of IPSec-based networks. The MIB has been designed to be adopted as an IETF standard. Hence vendor-specific features of IPSec protocol are excluded from this MIB. Acronyms The following acronyms are used in this document: IPsec: Secure IP Protocol VPN: Virtual Private Network ISAKMP: Internet Security Association and Key Exchange Protocol IKE: Internet Key Exchange Protocol SA: Security Association (ref: rfc2408). SPI: Security Parameter Index is the pointer or identifier used in accessing SA attributes (ref: rfc2408). MM: Main Mode - the process of setting up a Phase 1 SA to secure the exchanges required to setup Phase 2 SAs QM: Quick Mode - the process of setting up Phase 2 Security Associations using a Phase 1 SA. Phase 1 Tunnel: An ISAKMP SA can be regarded as representing a flow of ISAKMP/IKE traffic. Hence an ISAKMP is referred to as a 'Phase 1 Tunnel' in this document. Control Tunnel: Another term for a Phase 1 Tunnel. Phase 2 Tunnel: An instance of a non-ISAKMP SA bundle in which all the SA share the same proxy identifiers (IDii,IDir) protect the same stream of application traffic. Such an SA bundle is termed a 'Phase 2 Tunnel'. Note that a Phase 2 tunnel may comprise different SA bundles and different number of SA bundles at different times (due to key refresh). MTU: Maximum Transmission Unit (of an IPsec tunnel). History of the MIB A precursor to this MIB was written by Tivoli and implemented in IBM Nways routers in 1999. During late 1999, Cisco adopted the MIB and together with Tivoli publised the IPsec Flow Monitor MIB in IETF IPsec WG in draft-ietf-ipsec-flow-monitoring-mib-00.txt. In 2000, the MIB was Cisco-ized and implemented this draft as CISCO-IPSEC-FLOW-MONITOR-MIB in IOS and VPN3000 platforms. With the evolution of IKEv2, the MIB was modified and presented to the IPsec WG again in May 2003 in draft-ietf-ipsec-flow-monitoring-mib-02.txt. With the emergence of multiple IPsec signaling protocols, it became apparent that the signaling aspects of IPsec need to be instrumented separately in their own right. Thus, the IPsec control attributes and metrics were separated out into CISCO-IPSEC-SIGNALING-MIB and CISCO-IKE-FLOW-MIB. This version of the draft is the version of the draft that models that IPsec data protocol, structures and activity alone. Overview of MIB The MIB contains four major groups of objects which are used to manage the IPsec Protocol. These groups include a Levels Group, a Phase-1 Group, a Phase-2 Group, a History Group, a Failure Group and a TRAP Control Group. The following table illustrates the structure of the IPsec MIB. The Phase 2 group models objects pertaining to IPsec data tunnels. The History group is to aid applications that do trending analysis. The Failure group is to enable an operator to do troubleshooting and debugging of the VPN Router. Further, counters are supported to aid detection of potential security violations. In addition to the three major MIB Groups, there are a number of Notifications. The following table illustrates the name and description of the IPsec TRAPs.

ceipSecGlobalActiveTunnels.name: ceipSecGlobalActiveTunnels
ceipSecGlobalActiveTunnels.description: The total number of currently active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalPreviousTunnels.name: ceipSecGlobalPreviousTunnels
ceipSecGlobalPreviousTunnels.description: The total number of previously active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalInOctets.name: ceipSecGlobalInOctets
ceipSecGlobalInOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets received by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed.

ceipSecGlobalInDecompOctets.name: ceipSecGlobalInDecompOctets
ceipSecGlobalInDecompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of decompressed octets received by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ceipSecGlobalInOctets.

ceipSecGlobalInPkts.name: ceipSecGlobalInPkts
ceipSecGlobalInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalInDrops.name: ceipSecGlobalInDrops
ceipSecGlobalInDrops.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This count does NOT include packets dropped due to Anti-Replay processing.

ceipSecGlobalInReplayDrops.name: ceipSecGlobalInReplayDrops
ceipSecGlobalInReplayDrops.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing due to Anti-Replay processing by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalInAuths.name: ceipSecGlobalInAuths
ceipSecGlobalInAuths.description: The total number of inbound authentication's performed by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalInAuthFails.name: ceipSecGlobalInAuthFails
ceipSecGlobalInAuthFails.description: The total number of inbound authentication's which ended in failure by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalInDecrypts.name: ceipSecGlobalInDecrypts
ceipSecGlobalInDecrypts.description: The total number of inbound decryption's performed by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalInDecryptFails.name: ceipSecGlobalInDecryptFails
ceipSecGlobalInDecryptFails.description: The total number of inbound decryption's which ended in failure by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalOutOctets.name: ceipSecGlobalOutOctets
ceipSecGlobalOutOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets sent by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed.

ceipSecGlobalOutUncompOctets.name: ceipSecGlobalOutUncompOctets
ceipSecGlobalOutUncompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of uncompressed octets sent by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ceipSecGlobalOutOctets.

ceipSecGlobalOutPkts.name: ceipSecGlobalOutPkts
ceipSecGlobalOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalOutDrops.name: ceipSecGlobalOutDrops
ceipSecGlobalOutDrops.description: The total number of packets dropped during send processing by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalOutAuths.name: ceipSecGlobalOutAuths
ceipSecGlobalOutAuths.description: The total number of outbound authentication's performed by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalOutAuthFails.name: ceipSecGlobalOutAuthFails
ceipSecGlobalOutAuthFails.description: The total number of outbound authentication's which ended in failure by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalOutEncrypts.name: ceipSecGlobalOutEncrypts
ceipSecGlobalOutEncrypts.description: The total number of outbound encryption's performed by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecCertSubjectName.name: ceipSecCertSubjectName
ceipSecCertSubjectName.reference: RFC 3280 section 4.1.2.6 Subject RFC 3280 section 4.2.1.7 Subject Alternative Name
ceipSecCertSubjectName.description: This object provides the subject name from the X.509 certificate, or the alternate subject name if it is available. The subject name is formatted as a character string matching the output of a ssh-certview command-line application, except that the application sending the notification may limit the string length. Example Subject Name: C=US, OU=DEV, CN=Test-01 Example Subject Alternative Name: 2001:0022:0022:0020:0000:0000:0000:0102

ceipSecCertSerialNumber.name: ceipSecCertSerialNumber
ceipSecCertSerialNumber.description: This object provides the serial number from the X.509 certificate. The serial number is formatted as a character string matching the output of a ssh-certview command-line application. The issuer name and the serial number identify a unique certificate. Example: 1000655533

ceipSecCertIssuerName.name: ceipSecCertIssuerName
ceipSecCertIssuerName.description: This object provides the issuer name from the X.509 certificate. The issuer name is formatted as a character string matching the output of a ssh-certview command-line application, except that the application sending the notification may limit the string length. The issuer name and the serial number identify a unique certificate. Example: C=US, O=Cisco, OU=MITG, CN=Lnx-Insta-RootCA-1

ceipSecCertExpiryTime.name: ceipSecCertExpiryTime
ceipSecCertExpiryTime.description: This object provides the validity notAfter time from the X.509 certificate. The notAfter time is the time after which the certificate is not valid. The time is formatted as a character string matching the output of a ssh-certview command-line application. Example: 2012 Apr 14th, 19:01:45 GMT

ceipSecCertRenewalStatus.name: ceipSecCertRenewalStatus
ceipSecCertRenewalStatus.description: This object provides the renewal status of the X.509 certificate on the application sending the notification. renewalNotNeeded(1) = certificate is OK and does not need to be renewed renewalRequestNeeded(2) = certificate renewal request is needed renewalRequested(3) = certificate renewal has been requested and the renewal process is proceeding renewalSuccess(4) = certificate has been renewed and will be OK (renewalNotNeeded) renewalFailedUpdate(5) = certificate renewal failed, but certificate is still usable until the validity expiration time provided in the notification, or otherwise restricted by the application renewalFailedExpired(6) = certificate is no longer valid, the current time is after the certificate's validity notAfter time, which is provided in this notification

ceipSecCertExpiryStatus.name: ceipSecCertExpiryStatus
ceipSecCertExpiryStatus.description: This object provides the expiration status of the X.509 certificate on the application sending the notification. The notification is sent when the value of this object is changed from certOK(1) to certGoingExpired(2). certOK(1) = certificate is OK and is not within the configured time threshold for going to expire certGoingExpired(2) = certificate is within the configured time threshold for going to expire certExpired(3) = certificate has expired, the current time is after the certificate's validity notAfter time

ceipSecGlobalOutEncryptFails.name: ceipSecGlobalOutEncryptFails
ceipSecGlobalOutEncryptFails.description: The total number of outbound encryption's which ended in failure by all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalProtocolUseFails.name: ceipSecGlobalProtocolUseFails
ceipSecGlobalProtocolUseFails.description: The total number of protocol use failures which occurred during processing of all current and previously active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalNoSaFails.name: ceipSecGlobalNoSaFails
ceipSecGlobalNoSaFails.description: The total number of non-existent Security Association in failures which occurred during processing of all current and previous IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalSysCapFails.name: ceipSecGlobalSysCapFails
ceipSecGlobalSysCapFails.description: The total number of system capacity failures which occurred during processing of all current and previously active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels.

ceipSecGlobalOutCompressedPkts.name: ceipSecGlobalOutCompressedPkts
ceipSecGlobalOutCompressedPkts.description: The cumulative number of outbound packets across all IPsec flows terminating at this device which were successfully compressed.

ceipSecGlobalOutCompSkippedPkts.name: ceipSecGlobalOutCompSkippedPkts
ceipSecGlobalOutCompSkippedPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets across all IPsec flows terminating at this devices that were to be compressed but which were skipped due to the compression hysteresis.

ceipSecGlobalOutCompFailPkts.name: ceipSecGlobalOutCompFailPkts
ceipSecGlobalOutCompFailPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets across all IPsec flows terminating at this device that failed compression because they grew in size after compression.

ceipSecGlobalOutCompTooSmallPkts.name: ceipSecGlobalOutCompTooSmallPkts
ceipSecGlobalOutCompTooSmallPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets across all IPsec flows terminating at this device that were to be compressed but were smaller than the compression threshold size. This number is cumulative since the last system start.

ceipSecGlobalThroughputUtilizatioinTimeI.name: ceipSecGlobalThroughputUtilizatioinTimeInterval
ceipSecGlobalThroughputUtilizatioinTimeI.description: The object is the length of the time interval to measure the throughtput utilization.

ceipSecGlobalThroughputLastUpdatedTime.name: ceipSecGlobalThroughputLastUpdatedTime
ceipSecGlobalThroughputLastUpdatedTime.description: The timestamp is the end of the last throughput utilization time interval.

ceipSecGlobalLastAveragePacketSize.name: ceipSecGlobalLastAveragePacketSize
ceipSecGlobalLastAveragePacketSize.description: This object is the average packet size in the last throughput utilization time interval that ended at ceipSecGlobalThroughputLastUpdatedTime.

ceipSecGlobalLastThroughputInMbps.name: ceipSecGlobalLastThroughputInMbps
ceipSecGlobalLastThroughputInMbps.description: The object is the total throughput in Mbps in the last throughput utilization time interval that ended at ceipSecGlobalThroughputLastUpdatedTime.

ceipSecGlobalLastThroughputInKpps.name: ceipSecGlobalLastThroughputInKpps
ceipSecGlobalLastThroughputInKpps.description: The object is the total throughput in Kpps in the last throughput utilization time interval that ended at ceipSecGlobalThroughputLastUpdatedTime.

ceipSecGlobalLastThroughputUtilization.name: ceipSecGlobalLastThroughputUtilization
ceipSecGlobalLastThroughputUtilization.description: The object is the throughput utilization in percentage in the last performance utilization time interval that ended at ceipSecGlobalThroughputLastUpdatedTime.

ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputUtilization.name: ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputUtilization
ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputUtilization.description: The object is the peak throughput utilization in percentage since the managed system is active. It was observed in the throughput utilization time interval that ended at ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputDateAndTime.

ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputDateAndTime.name: ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputDateAndTime
ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputDateAndTime.description: The date and time when ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputUtilization is updated.

ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputInMbps.name: ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputInMbps
ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputInMbps.description: The object indicates the peak value of throughput in Mbps.

ceipSecGlobalPeakAvgPacketSize.name: ceipSecGlobalPeakAvgPacketSize
ceipSecGlobalPeakAvgPacketSize.description: This object indicates the average packet size in bytes in the throughput utilization time interval that ended at ceipSecGlobalPeakThroughputDateAndTime.

ceipSecTunnelTable.name: ceipSecTunnelTable
ceipSecTunnelTable.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Table. There is one entry in this table for each active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunnelEntry.name: ceipSecTunnelEntry
ceipSecTunnelEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with an active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunIndex.name: ceipSecTunIndex
ceipSecTunIndex.description: The index of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Table. The value of the index is a number which begins at 1 and is incremented with each tunnel that is created. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647. Since this object must correspond to a valid Phase-2 IPsec tunnel, this object may not assume the value of 0.

ceipSecTunLocalAddressType.name: ceipSecTunLocalAddressType
ceipSecTunLocalAddressType.description: The type of the IP address of the local endpoint for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunLocalAddress.name: ceipSecTunLocalAddress
ceipSecTunLocalAddress.description: The IP address of the local endpoint for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunRemoteAddressType.name: ceipSecTunRemoteAddressType
ceipSecTunRemoteAddressType.description: The type of the IP address of the remote endpoint for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunRemoteAddress.name: ceipSecTunRemoteAddress
ceipSecTunRemoteAddress.description: The IP address of the remote endpoint for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunControlProtocol.name: ceipSecTunControlProtocol
ceipSecTunControlProtocol.description: Identifies the protocol used to setup and administer this Phase-2 IPsec tunnel. In case this tunnel was spawned by an IPsec signaling protocol, this MIB object contains the value of the object 'cisgIpsSgProtocol' defined in CISCO-IPSEC-SIGNALING-MIB in the table 'cisgIpsSgTunnelTable' in the row corresponding to the control tunnel. A value of 'cpManual' is indicative of a manually installed and administered Phase-2 tunnel.

ceipSecTunControlTunnelIndex.name: ceipSecTunControlTunnelIndex
ceipSecTunControlTunnelIndex.description: The index of the associated IPsec Phase-1 Tunnel. In case this tunnel was spawned by an IPsec signaling protocol, this MIB object contains the value of the object 'cisgIpsSgTunIndex' defined in CISCO-IPSEC-SIGNALING-MIB in the table 'cisgIpsSgTunnelTable' in the row corresponding to the control tunnel. A value of 0 identifies that this Phase-2 tunnel was setup manually.

ceipSecTunControlTunnelAlive.name: ceipSecTunControlTunnelAlive
ceipSecTunControlTunnelAlive.description: An indicator which specifies whether or not the IPsec Phase-1 Tunnel that spawned this Phase-2 tunnel currently exists.

ceipSecTunEncapMode.name: ceipSecTunEncapMode
ceipSecTunEncapMode.description: The encapsulation mode used by the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunNATTraversalMode.name: ceipSecTunNATTraversalMode
ceipSecTunNATTraversalMode.description: The encapsulation used by the IPsec Phase-2 tunnel for NAT traversal. The value of this object is constrained based on the value of the column 'ceipSecTunEncapMode'. If the value of 'ceipSecTunEncapMode' is 'encapTransport', then this object may not assume the values 'natEncapIPsecOverUdp' or 'natEncapIPsecOverTcp'.

ceipSecTunLifeSize.name: ceipSecTunLifeSize
ceipSecTunLifeSize.description: The negotiated LifeSize of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel in kilobytes.

ceipSecTunLifeTime.name: ceipSecTunLifeTime
ceipSecTunLifeTime.description: The negotiated LifeTime of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel in seconds. If the tunnel was setup manually, the value of this MIB element should be 0.

ceipSecTunActiveTime.name: ceipSecTunActiveTime
ceipSecTunActiveTime.description: The length of time the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel has been active in hundredths of seconds.

ceipSecTunSaLifeSizeThreshold.name: ceipSecTunSaLifeSizeThreshold
ceipSecTunSaLifeSizeThreshold.description: The security association LifeSize refresh threshold in kilobytes. If the tunnel was setup manually, the value of this MIB element should be 0.

ceipSecTunSaLifeTimeThreshold.name: ceipSecTunSaLifeTimeThreshold
ceipSecTunSaLifeTimeThreshold.description: The security association LifeTime refresh threshold in seconds. If the tunnel was setup manually, the value of this MIB element should be 0.

ceipSecTunTotalRefreshes.name: ceipSecTunTotalRefreshes
ceipSecTunTotalRefreshes.description: The total number of security association refreshes performed.

ceipSecTunExpiredSaInstances.name: ceipSecTunExpiredSaInstances
ceipSecTunExpiredSaInstances.description: The total number of security associations which have expired. If the tunnel was setup manually, the value of this MIB element should be 0.

ceipSecTunCurrentSaInstances.name: ceipSecTunCurrentSaInstances
ceipSecTunCurrentSaInstances.description: The number of security associations which are currently active or expiring.

ceipSecTunInSaDHGrp.name: ceipSecTunInSaDHGrp
ceipSecTunInSaDHGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. If the tunnel was setup manually, the value of this MIB element would be `none'.

ceipSecTunInSaEncryptAlgo.name: ceipSecTunInSaEncryptAlgo
ceipSecTunInSaEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunInSaEncryptKeySize.name: ceipSecTunInSaEncryptKeySize
ceipSecTunInSaEncryptKeySize.description: The key size in bits of the negotiated key to be used with the algorithm denoted by 'ceipSecTunInSaEncryptAlgo'. For DES and 3DES the key size is respectively 56 and 168. For AES, this will denote the negotiated key size.

ceipSecTunInSaAhAuthAlgo.name: ceipSecTunInSaAhAuthAlgo
ceipSecTunInSaAhAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound authentication header (AH) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunInSaEspAuthAlgo.name: ceipSecTunInSaEspAuthAlgo
ceipSecTunInSaEspAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound ecapsulation security protocol (ESP) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunInSaDecompAlgo.name: ceipSecTunInSaDecompAlgo
ceipSecTunInSaDecompAlgo.description: The decompression algorithm used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunOutSaDHGrp.name: ceipSecTunOutSaDHGrp
ceipSecTunOutSaDHGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used by the outbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. If the tunnel was setup manually, the value of this MIB element would be 'none'.

ceipSecTunOutSaEncryptAlgo.name: ceipSecTunOutSaEncryptAlgo
ceipSecTunOutSaEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used by the outbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunOutSaEncryptKeySize.name: ceipSecTunOutSaEncryptKeySize
ceipSecTunOutSaEncryptKeySize.description: The key size in bits of the negotiated key to be used with the algorithm denoted by 'ceipSecTunOutSaEncryptAlgo'. For DES and 3DES the key size is respectively 56 and 168. For AES, this will denote the negotiated key size.

ceipSecTunOutSaAhAuthAlgo.name: ceipSecTunOutSaAhAuthAlgo
ceipSecTunOutSaAhAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the outbound authentication header (AH) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunOutSaEspAuthAlgo.name: ceipSecTunOutSaEspAuthAlgo
ceipSecTunOutSaEspAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound encapsulation security protocol (ESP) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunOutSaCompAlgo.name: ceipSecTunOutSaCompAlgo
ceipSecTunOutSaCompAlgo.description: The compression algorithm used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunPmtu.name: ceipSecTunPmtu
ceipSecTunPmtu.description: The Path MTU for this IPsec Phase-2 tunnel, which has been either learnt from the network or which has been specified by the administrator. The lower end of the range is 68 which is the minimum MTU for IPv4.

ceipSecTunInOctets.name: ceipSecTunInOctets
ceipSecTunInOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed.

ceipSecTunInDecompOctets.name: ceipSecTunInDecompOctets
ceipSecTunInDecompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of decompressed octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ceipSecTunInOctets.

ceipSecTunInPkts.name: ceipSecTunInPkts
ceipSecTunInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunInDropPkts.name: ceipSecTunInDropPkts
ceipSecTunInDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This count does NOT include packets dropped due to Anti-Replay processing.

ceipSecTunInReplayDropPkts.name: ceipSecTunInReplayDropPkts
ceipSecTunInReplayDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing due to Anti-Replay processing by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunInAuths.name: ceipSecTunInAuths
ceipSecTunInAuths.description: The total number of inbound authentication's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunInAuthFails.name: ceipSecTunInAuthFails
ceipSecTunInAuthFails.description: The total number of inbound authentication's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel .

ceipSecTunInDecrypts.name: ceipSecTunInDecrypts
ceipSecTunInDecrypts.description: The total number of inbound decryption's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunInDecryptFails.name: ceipSecTunInDecryptFails
ceipSecTunInDecryptFails.description: The total number of inbound decryption's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunOutOctets.name: ceipSecTunOutOctets
ceipSecTunOutOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed.

ceipSecTunOutUncompOctets.name: ceipSecTunOutUncompOctets
ceipSecTunOutUncompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of uncompressed octets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ceipSecTunOutOctets.

ceipSecTunOutPkts.name: ceipSecTunOutPkts
ceipSecTunOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunOutDropPkts.name: ceipSecTunOutDropPkts
ceipSecTunOutDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during send processing by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunOutAuths.name: ceipSecTunOutAuths
ceipSecTunOutAuths.description: The total number of outbound authentication's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunOutAuthFails.name: ceipSecTunOutAuthFails
ceipSecTunOutAuthFails.description: The total number of outbound authentication's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunOutEncrypts.name: ceipSecTunOutEncrypts
ceipSecTunOutEncrypts.description: The total number of outbound encryption's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunOutEncryptFails.name: ceipSecTunOutEncryptFails
ceipSecTunOutEncryptFails.description: The total number of outbound encryption's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunOutCompressedPkts.name: ceipSecTunOutCompressedPkts
ceipSecTunOutCompressedPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets which were successfully compressed.

ceipSecTunOutCompSkippedPkts.name: ceipSecTunOutCompSkippedPkts
ceipSecTunOutCompSkippedPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets that were to be compressed but which were skipped due to the compression hysteresis.

ceipSecTunOutCompFailPkts.name: ceipSecTunOutCompFailPkts
ceipSecTunOutCompFailPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets that failed compression because they grew in size after compression.

ceipSecTunOutCompTooSmallPkts.name: ceipSecTunOutCompTooSmallPkts
ceipSecTunOutCompTooSmallPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets that were to be compressed but were smaller than the compression threshold size.

ceipSecIfIndex.name: ceipSecIfIndex
ceipSecIfIndex.description: This object represents the ifIndex of an interface where this tunnel is created. Multiple IPsec tunnels can be created using the same interface.

ceipSecTunStatus.name: ceipSecTunStatus
ceipSecTunStatus.description: The status of the MIB table row. This object can be used to bring the tunnel down or force a rekeying. When the value is set to destroy(5), the SA bundle is destroyed and this row is deleted from this table. When the value is set to rekey(6), then rekeying is forced on this tunnel. When this MIB value is queried, the value of active(4) is always returned, if the instance exists. This object cannot be used to create a MIB table row.

ceipSecEndPtTable.name: ceipSecEndPtTable
ceipSecEndPtTable.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Endpoint Table. This table contains an entry for each active endpoint associated with an IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecEndPtEntry.name: ceipSecEndPtEntry
ceipSecEndPtEntry.description: An IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Endpoint entry.

ceipSecEndPtIndex.name: ceipSecEndPtIndex
ceipSecEndPtIndex.description: The number of the Endpoint associated with the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Table. The value of this index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each Endpoint associated with an IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. The value of this object will wrap at 4,294,967,295.

ceipSecEndPtLocalName.name: ceipSecEndPtLocalName
ceipSecEndPtLocalName.description: The DNS name of the local Endpoint.

ceipSecEndPtLocalType.name: ceipSecEndPtLocalType
ceipSecEndPtLocalType.description: The type of identity for the local Endpoint.

ceipSecEndPtLocalAddrType1.name: ceipSecEndPtLocalAddrType1
ceipSecEndPtLocalAddrType1.description: The type of the IP address for this local Endpoint's first IP address.

ceipSecEndPtLocalAddr1.name: ceipSecEndPtLocalAddr1
ceipSecEndPtLocalAddr1.description: The local Endpoint's first IP address specification. If the local Endpoint type is single IP address, then this is the value of the IP address. If the local Endpoint type is IP subnet, then this is the value of the subnet. If the local Endpoint type is IP address range, then this is the value of beginning IP address of the range. If the type is an IP address, a range or a subnet, the type of the address can be inferred from ceipSecEndPtLocalType.

ceipSecEndPtLocalAddrType2.name: ceipSecEndPtLocalAddrType2
ceipSecEndPtLocalAddrType2.description: The type of the IP address for this local Endpoint's second IP address.

ceipSecEndPtLocalAddr2.name: ceipSecEndPtLocalAddr2

If the local Endpoint type is IP subnet, then this is the value of the subnet mask. If the local Endpoint type is IP address range, then this is the value of ending IP address of the range. If the type is an IP address, a range or a subnet, the type of the address can be inferred from ceipSecEndPtLocalType.

ceipSecEndPtLocalProtocol.name: ceipSecEndPtLocalProtocol
ceipSecEndPtLocalProtocol.description: The protocol number of the local Endpoint's traffic.

ceipSecEndPtLocalPort.name: ceipSecEndPtLocalPort
ceipSecEndPtLocalPort.description: The port number of the local Endpoint's traffic.

ceipSecEndPtRemoteName.name: ceipSecEndPtRemoteName
ceipSecEndPtRemoteName.description: The DNS name of the remote Endpoint.

ceipSecEndPtRemoteType.name: ceipSecEndPtRemoteType
ceipSecEndPtRemoteType.description: The type of identity for the remote Endpoint.

ceipSecEndPtRemoteAddrType1.name: ceipSecEndPtRemoteAddrType1
ceipSecEndPtRemoteAddrType1.description: The type of the IP address for this remote Endpoint's first IP address.

ceipSecEndPtRemoteAddr1.name: ceipSecEndPtRemoteAddr1

ceipSecEndPtRemoteAddrType2.name: ceipSecEndPtRemoteAddrType2
ceipSecEndPtRemoteAddrType2.description: The type of the IP address for this remote Endpoint's second IP address.

ceipSecEndPtRemoteAddr2.name: ceipSecEndPtRemoteAddr2

ceipSecEndPtRemoteProtocol.name: ceipSecEndPtRemoteProtocol
ceipSecEndPtRemoteProtocol.description: The protocol number of the remote Endpoint's traffic.

ceipSecEndPtRemotePort.name: ceipSecEndPtRemotePort
ceipSecEndPtRemotePort.description: The port number of the remote Endpoint's traffic.

ceipSecSaTable.name: ceipSecSaTable
ceipSecSaTable.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Security Association Table. This table identifies the structure (in terms of component SAs) of each active Phase-2 IPsec tunnel. This table contains an entry for each active and expiring security association and maps each entry in the active Phase-2 tunnel table (ceipSecTunTable) into a number of entries in this table. The index of this table reflects the <destination-address, protocol, spi> rule for identifying Security Associations.

ceipSecSaEntry.name: ceipSecSaEntry
ceipSecSaEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with active and expiring IPsec Phase-2 security associations.

ceipSecSaProtocol.name: ceipSecSaProtocol
ceipSecSaProtocol.description: This column represents the security protocol (AH, ESP or IPComp) for which this security association was setup.

ceipSecSaIndex.name: ceipSecSaIndex
ceipSecSaIndex.description: The object, in the context of the IPsec tunnel 'ceipSecTunIndex', is an index of security associations comprising the Phase-2 IPsec tunnel represented by the tunnel index 'ceipSecTunIndex'. The value of this index is a number which begins at 1 and is incremented with each SPI associated with the corresponding IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecSaDirection.name: ceipSecSaDirection
ceipSecSaDirection.description: Phase-2 IPsec security associations are simplex. Hence a particular security association is used either for securing outgoing traffic or decoding incoming traffic. This column identifies the direction of the security association represented by this entry.

ceipSecSaValue.name: ceipSecSaValue
ceipSecSaValue.description: This is the value of the Security Protection Index (SPI) assigned by the system to the security association represented by this entry.

ceipSecSaStatus.name: ceipSecSaStatus
ceipSecSaStatus.description: This column represents the status of the security association represented by this conceptual row. If the status of the SA is 'active', the SA is ready for active use. The status 'expiring' represents any of the various states that the security association transitions through before being purged.

ceipSecTunnelSaTable.name: ceipSecTunnelSaTable
ceipSecTunnelSaTable.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel Security Association Table. This table identifies the SAs that are currently associated with an active Phase-2 tunnel. This table contains an entry for each active or expiring security association (SA) which is associated with an ceipSecTunnelEntry in 'active' state and provides statistic information of this SA. There might be multiple SAs associated with one ceipSecTunnelEntry.

ceipSecTunnelSaEntry.name: ceipSecTunnelSaEntry
ceipSecTunnelSaEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes and statistics associated with an active or expiring IPsec Phase-2 security associations.

ceipSecTunSaProtocol.name: ceipSecTunSaProtocol
ceipSecTunSaProtocol.description: This column represents the security protocol (AH, ESP or IPComp) for which this security association was setup.

ceipSecTunSaIndex.name: ceipSecTunSaIndex
ceipSecTunSaIndex.description: The object, in the context of the IPsec tunnel 'ceipSecTunIndex', is an index of security associations comprising the Phase-2 IPsec tunnel represented by the tunnel index 'ceipSecTunIndex'. The value of this index is a number which begins at 1 and is incremented with each SPI associated with the corresponding IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunSaDirection.name: ceipSecTunSaDirection
ceipSecTunSaDirection.description: Phase-2 IPsec security associations are simplex. Hence a particular security association is used either for securing outgoing traffic or decoding incoming traffic. This column identifies the direction of the security association represented by this entry.

ceipSecTunSaValue.name: ceipSecTunSaValue
ceipSecTunSaValue.description: This is the value of the Security Protection Index (SPI) assigned by the system to the security association represented by this entry.

ceipSecTunSaIfIndex.name: ceipSecTunSaIfIndex
ceipSecTunSaIfIndex.description: This object represents the ifIndex of an interface where a tunnel with ceipSecTunIndex is created. Multiple IPsec tunnels can be created using the same interface.

ceipSecTunSaInOctets.name: ceipSecTunSaInOctets
ceipSecTunSaInOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets received by using this SA. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed.

ceipSecTunSaInDecompOctets.name: ceipSecTunSaInDecompOctets
ceipSecTunSaInDecompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of decompressed octets received by using this SA. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ceipSecTunSaTunInOctets.

ceipSecTunSaInPkts.name: ceipSecTunSaInPkts
ceipSecTunSaInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaInDropPkts.name: ceipSecTunSaInDropPkts
ceipSecTunSaInDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive process by using this SA. This count does NOT include packets dropped due to Anti-Replay processing.

ceipSecTunSaInReplayDropPkts.name: ceipSecTunSaInReplayDropPkts
ceipSecTunSaInReplayDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing due to Anti-Replay processing by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaInAuths.name: ceipSecTunSaInAuths
ceipSecTunSaInAuths.description: The total number of inbound authentication's performed by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaInAuthFails.name: ceipSecTunSaInAuthFails
ceipSecTunSaInAuthFails.description: The total number of inbound authentication's which ended in failure by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaInDecrypts.name: ceipSecTunSaInDecrypts
ceipSecTunSaInDecrypts.description: The total number of inbound decryption's performed by this SA.

ceipSecTunSaInDecryptFails.name: ceipSecTunSaInDecryptFails
ceipSecTunSaInDecryptFails.description: The total number of inbound decryption's which ended in failure by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaOutOctets.name: ceipSecTunSaOutOctets
ceipSecTunSaOutOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets sent by using this SA. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed.

ceipSecTunSaOutUncompOctets.name: ceipSecTunSaOutUncompOctets
ceipSecTunSaOutUncompOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of uncompressed octets sent by using this SA. This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed. If compression is not being used, this value will match the value of ceipSecTunSaTunOutOctets.

ceipSecTunSaOutPkts.name: ceipSecTunSaOutPkts
ceipSecTunSaOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaOutDropPkts.name: ceipSecTunSaOutDropPkts
ceipSecTunSaOutDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during send processing by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaOutAuths.name: ceipSecTunSaOutAuths
ceipSecTunSaOutAuths.description: The total number of outbound authentication's performed by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaOutAuthFails.name: ceipSecTunSaOutAuthFails
ceipSecTunSaOutAuthFails.description: The total number of outbound authentication's which ended in failure by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaOutEncrypts.name: ceipSecTunSaOutEncrypts
ceipSecTunSaOutEncrypts.description: The total number of outbound encryption's performed by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaOutEncryptFails.name: ceipSecTunSaOutEncryptFails
ceipSecTunSaOutEncryptFails.description: The total number of outbound encryption's which ended in failure by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaOutCompressedPkts.name: ceipSecTunSaOutCompressedPkts
ceipSecTunSaOutCompressedPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets which were successfully compressed by using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaOutCompSkippedPkts.name: ceipSecTunSaOutCompSkippedPkts
ceipSecTunSaOutCompSkippedPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets that were to be compressed but which were skipped due to the compression hysteresis when using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaOutCompFailPkts.name: ceipSecTunSaOutCompFailPkts
ceipSecTunSaOutCompFailPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets that failed compression because they grew in size after compression when using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaOutCompTooSmallPkts.name: ceipSecTunSaOutCompTooSmallPkts
ceipSecTunSaOutCompTooSmallPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets that were to be compressed but were smaller than the compression threshold size when using this SA.

ceipSecTunSaStatus.name: ceipSecTunSaStatus
ceipSecTunSaStatus.description: This column represents the status of the security association represented by this conceptual row. If the status of the SA is 'active', the SA is ready for active use. The status 'expiring' represents any of the various states that the security association transitions through before being purged.

ceipSecIfTunnelTable.name: ceipSecIfTunnelTable
ceipSecIfTunnelTable.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels to Interface association table. This table contains an entry for each active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel created under an interface. Multiple IPsec Phase-2 Tunnels can be created using the same interface.

ceipSecIfTunnelEntry.name: ceipSecIfTunnelEntry
ceipSecIfTunnelEntry.description: Each entry contains the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel associated with an interface.

ceipSecIfTunnelStatus.name: ceipSecIfTunnelStatus
ceipSecIfTunnelStatus.description: This object corresponds to the status of a IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel in ceipSecTunnelTable indexed by ceipSecTunIndex. The valid status this object can have are 'active' and 'awaitCommit'.

ceipSecHistTableSize.name: ceipSecHistTableSize
ceipSecHistTableSize.description: The window size of the IPsec Phase-2 History Tables. The IPsec Phase-2 History Tables are implemented as a sliding window in which only the last 'N' entries are maintained. This object is used specify the number of entries which will be maintained in the IPsec Phase-2 History Tables. An implementation may choose suitable minimum and maximum values for this element based on the local policy and available resources. If an SNMP SET request specifies a value outside this window for this element, in appropriate SNMP error code should be returned. Setting this value to zero is equivalent to deleting all conceptual rows in the archiving tables ('ceipSecHistTable' and 'ceipSecEndPtHistTable') and disabling the archiving of entries in the tables.

ceipSecTunnelHistTable.name: ceipSecTunnelHistTable
ceipSecTunnelHistTable.description: The IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel History Table. This table is conceptually a sliding window in which only the last 'N' entries are maintained, where 'N' is the value of the object 'ceipSecHistTableSize'. If the value of 'ceipSecHistTableSize' is 0, archiving of entries in this table is disabled.

ceipSecTunnelHistEntry.name: ceipSecTunnelHistEntry
ceipSecTunnelHistEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with a previously active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistIndex.name: ceipSecTunHistIndex
ceipSecTunHistIndex.description: The index of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel History Table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that ends. The value of this object will wrap at 4,294,967,295.

ceipSecTunHistTermReason.name: ceipSecTunHistTermReason
ceipSecTunHistTermReason.description: The reason the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel was terminated. Possible reasons include: 1 = other 2 = normal termination 3 = operator request 4 = peer delete request was received 5 = contact with peer was lost 6 = applicationInitiated (eg: L2TP requesting the termination) 7 = failure of extended authentication 8 = local failure occurred 9 = operator initiated check point request

ceipSecTunHistActiveIndex.name: ceipSecTunHistActiveIndex
ceipSecTunHistActiveIndex.description: The index of the previously active IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This object must correspond to an expired IPsec tunnel; hence this object may not assume the value of 0.

ceipSecTunHistLocalAddressType.name: ceipSecTunHistLocalAddressType
ceipSecTunHistLocalAddressType.description: The type of the IP address of the local endpoint for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistLocalAddress.name: ceipSecTunHistLocalAddress
ceipSecTunHistLocalAddress.description: The IP address of the local endpoint for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistRemoteAddressType.name: ceipSecTunHistRemoteAddressType
ceipSecTunHistRemoteAddressType.description: The type of the IP address of the remote endpoint for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistRemoteAddress.name: ceipSecTunHistRemoteAddress
ceipSecTunHistRemoteAddress.description: The IP address of the remote endpoint for the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistControlProtocol.name: ceipSecTunHistControlProtocol
ceipSecTunHistControlProtocol.description: Identifies the protocol that was used to setup and administer Phase-2 IPsec tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistControlTunnelIndex.name: ceipSecTunHistControlTunnelIndex
ceipSecTunHistControlTunnelIndex.description: The index of the IPsec Phase-1 Tunnel that spawned this Phase-2 tunnel (in case of IKE, this value would refer to 'csikeTunIndex' in the 'csikeTunnelTable'). If the IPsec tunnel corresponding to this entry was setup manually, the value of this object should be zero.

ceipSecTunHistEncapMode.name: ceipSecTunHistEncapMode
ceipSecTunHistEncapMode.description: The encapsulation mode used by the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistNATTraversalMode.name: ceipSecTunHistNATTraversalMode
ceipSecTunHistNATTraversalMode.description: The encapsulation used by the IPsec Phase-2 tunnel corresponding to this conceptual row for NAT traversal.

ceipSecTunHistLifeSize.name: ceipSecTunHistLifeSize
ceipSecTunHistLifeSize.description: The negotiated LifeSize of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel in kilobytes.

ceipSecTunHistLifeTime.name: ceipSecTunHistLifeTime
ceipSecTunHistLifeTime.description: The negotiated LifeTime of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel in seconds.

ceipSecTunHistStartTime.name: ceipSecTunHistStartTime
ceipSecTunHistStartTime.description: The value of sysUpTime in hundredths of seconds when the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel was started.

ceipSecTunHistActiveTime.name: ceipSecTunHistActiveTime
ceipSecTunHistActiveTime.description: The length of time the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel has been active in hundredths of seconds.

ceipSecTunHistTotalRefreshes.name: ceipSecTunHistTotalRefreshes
ceipSecTunHistTotalRefreshes.description: The total number of security association refreshes performed.

ceipSecTunHistTotalSas.name: ceipSecTunHistTotalSas
ceipSecTunHistTotalSas.description: The total number of security associations used during the life of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistInSaDHGrp.name: ceipSecTunHistInSaDHGrp
ceipSecTunHistInSaDHGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistInSaEncryptAlgo.name: ceipSecTunHistInSaEncryptAlgo
ceipSecTunHistInSaEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistInSaEncryptKeySize.name: ceipSecTunHistInSaEncryptKeySize
ceipSecTunHistInSaEncryptKeySize.description: The size in bits of the key which was negotiated to be used with the encryption transform used with this tunnel denoted by ceipSecTunHistInSaEncryptAlgo. For DES and 3DES the key size is respectively 56 and 168. For AES, this will denote the negotiated key size.

ceipSecTunHistInSaAhAuthAlgo.name: ceipSecTunHistInSaAhAuthAlgo
ceipSecTunHistInSaAhAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound authentication header (AH) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistInSaEspAuthAlgo.name: ceipSecTunHistInSaEspAuthAlgo
ceipSecTunHistInSaEspAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound encapsulation security protocol (ESP) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistInSaDecompAlgo.name: ceipSecTunHistInSaDecompAlgo
ceipSecTunHistInSaDecompAlgo.description: The decompression algorithm used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistOutSaDHGrp.name: ceipSecTunHistOutSaDHGrp
ceipSecTunHistOutSaDHGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used by the outbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistOutSaEncryptAlgo.name: ceipSecTunHistOutSaEncryptAlgo
ceipSecTunHistOutSaEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used by the outbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistOutSaEncryptKeySz.name: ceipSecTunHistOutSaEncryptKeySz
ceipSecTunHistOutSaEncryptKeySz.description: The size in bits of the key which was negotiated to be used with the encryption transform used with this tunnel denoted by ceipSecTunHistOutSaEncryptAlgo. For DES and 3DES the key size is respectively 56 and 168. For AES, this will denote the negotiated key size.

ceipSecTunHistOutSaAhAuthAlgo.name: ceipSecTunHistOutSaAhAuthAlgo
ceipSecTunHistOutSaAhAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the outbound authentication header (AH) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistOutSaEspAuthAlgo.name: ceipSecTunHistOutSaEspAuthAlgo
ceipSecTunHistOutSaEspAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound ecapsulation security protocol (ESP) security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistOutSaCompAlgo.name: ceipSecTunHistOutSaCompAlgo
ceipSecTunHistOutSaCompAlgo.description: The compression algorithm used by the inbound security association of the IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistPmtu.name: ceipSecTunHistPmtu
ceipSecTunHistPmtu.description: The Path MTU that was determined for this IPsec Phase-2 tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistInOctets.name: ceipSecTunHistInOctets
ceipSecTunHistInOctets.description: A high capacity count of the total number of octets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed.

ceipSecTunHistInPkts.name: ceipSecTunHistInPkts
ceipSecTunHistInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistInDropPkts.name: ceipSecTunHistInDropPkts
ceipSecTunHistInDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel. This count does NOT include packets dropped due to Anti-Replay processing.

ceipSecTunHistInReplayDropPkts.name: ceipSecTunHistInReplayDropPkts
ceipSecTunHistInReplayDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during receive processing due to Anti-Replay processing by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistInAuths.name: ceipSecTunHistInAuths
ceipSecTunHistInAuths.description: The total number of inbound authentication's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistInAuthFails.name: ceipSecTunHistInAuthFails
ceipSecTunHistInAuthFails.description: The total number of inbound authentication's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel .

ceipSecTunHistInDecrypts.name: ceipSecTunHistInDecrypts
ceipSecTunHistInDecrypts.description: The total number of inbound decryption's performed by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistInDecryptFails.name: ceipSecTunHistInDecryptFails
ceipSecTunHistInDecryptFails.description: The total number of inbound decryption's which ended in failure by this IPsec Phase-2 Tunnel.

ceipSecTunHistOutOctets.name: ceipSecTunHistOutOctets

ceipSecTunHistOutCompressedPkts.description: The total number of outbound packets which were successfully compressed.

ceipSecTunHistOutCompSkippedPkts.name: ceipSecTunHistOutCompSkippedPkts

ceipSecTunHistOutCompFailPkts.name: ceipSecTunHistOutCompFailPkts
